  Assignment

It's time for your final assignment!

This week is all about bringing all of the concepts you've learned together into a cohesive film. Here are the details:

Your Assignment: Create a 30+ Second Film

  • Create a short film that tells a narrative story. It needs to be at least 30 seconds long.
  • You can cover any genre or topic that interests you.
  • You can use voice-over, narration, characters talking, or vocal-free production. The choice is entirely up to you.
  • Include at least one advanced topic learned this week:
    • Advanced Face Compositing in MyHeritage
    • Animated Object Isolation and Animation
    • A Looping Background Using Loopflow
    • The Puppet Tool
    • Generative Prompt-to-Video Using Runway
  • Try to keep shots consistent in tone and style. Everything should feel like it belongs together.
  • Include camera movements that feature paralaxing.
  • Bring it all together with music and sound effects.

When you're ready to turn in your assignment, you can upload it to the week 4 assignment channel or share a link.
